        <body>
            <p rend="indent(9)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <date>Jay 5 / 53</date>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Rev. Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">I beg to acknowledge<lb/> Recpt of your Esteed note of the
                    <date>29th</date> ult<lb/> particularly note the contents</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I beg to say try no, as you well<lb/> know, I have not only a large
                family<lb/> but sisters &amp; aunt to support and<lb/> the claims upon me are
                heavy<lb/> I therefore regret I cannot<lb/> comply unto your request to<lb/> grant a
                pension of $200 or $300<lb/> p year to <persName>Miss Judah</persName></p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I spake with <persName>Mr David Judah</persName><lb/> the last time
                I was in <placeName>Baltimore</placeName><lb/> relative to <persName>Miss
                    Judah</persName>: he is a simple<lb/> man, but himself to support &amp;
                    <add>?</add><lb/> I believe has extend relief to her,<lb/> and I can hardly
                think she is<lb/> in such great distress as you<lb/> apprehend</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">Your friend &amp; se</p>
            <p rend="indent(6)">
                <persName role="author">M C Mordecai</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
    </text>
